  "prompt": "How common is using \"ex\" as the short for \"example\"?",
  "response": "The abbreviation \"ex\" is sometimes used informally to mean \"example,\" but it's not as commonly used or recognized as other abbreviations for \"example,\" such as \"e.g.\" or \"ex.\" In formal writing, \"e.g.\" is more standard and widely accepted. \"Ex\" might be seen in casual contexts, like text messages or informal notes, but using \"e.g.\" or writing out \"example\" is generally safer for clarity and formality.",
